---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/base.astro";
const title = "Koichi Nakayamada";
const h1 = "Hello, I'm Koichi";

const birthDate = new Date(2004, 11, 9); // December 9, 2004
const today = new Date();
const age =
    today.getFullYear() -
    birthDate.getFullYear() -
    (today <
    new Date(today.getFullYear(), birthDate.getMonth(), birthDate.getDate())
        ? 1
        : 0);
---

<BaseLayout title={title} h1={h1}>
    <p class="mb-8 sm:mb-12 text-base text-(--color-text-second) dark:text-(--color-text-second-dark) leading-relaxed">
        I'm a {age}-year-old Japanese Data Science undergraduate student who finds beauty in the intersection of numbers and code.
        Currently, I'm exploring the vast landscapes of machine learning while keeping my roots firmly planted in the terminal.
        My journey into the world of software began with a simple curiosity that has since evolved into a full-blown passion for building meaningful tools.
        I'm particularly interested in how we can make data more accessible and intuitive through thoughtful design and robust engineering.
        Lately, I've been experimenting with generative art and procedural generation, finding it a fascinating way to visualize complex mathematical concepts.
        When I'm not training models or refactoring scripts, you can usually find me documenting my latest discoveries.
        Feel free to <a href="/writing" class="underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-(--color-accent-light) dark:hover:text-(--color-accent-dark) transition-colors duration-200">check out my writing</a> where I share technical deep-dives and personal reflections.
        I believe that every problem is an opportunity to learn something new and every bug is a puzzle waiting to be solved.
        My digital garden is a work in progress, much like my understanding of the complex algorithms I study daily.
        Beyond the screen, I'm an avid reader of classic literature and a fan of minimalist aesthetics in both physical and digital spaces.
        I find that stepping away from the keyboard often provides the clearest insights into the most stubborn coding challenges.
        You can also catch me sharing quick updates and tech snippets over on <a href="https://twitter.com/koichincom" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-(--color-accent-light) dark:hover:text-(--color-accent-dark) transition-colors duration-200">Twitter</a>.
        Whether it's optimizing a SQL query or tweaking a CSS animation, I strive for elegance and efficiency in everything I create.
        I'm always open to interesting conversations, whether they're about data architecture or the best terminal themes.
        Thanks for stopping by my little corner of the internet; let's build something incredible together.
    </p>
</BaseLayout>
